<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF98FF97E9FBFCC6FE30FC1B" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF98FF97E9FBFCC6FE30FC1B" blockId="7.[151,1436,782,1167]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97E9FBFCC6FEDBFCE7" bold="true" box="[199,334,854,879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Etymology.</emphasis>
Noun in apposition taken from 
<typeStatus id="7117882DFF98FF97EB84FCC7FD7DFCE7" box="[696,744,855,879]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">type</typeStatus>
locality. The final -n is added in order to mimic phonetics of the name of the locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF98FF97E9FBFC0EFB93FB07" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF98FF97E9FBFC0EFB93FB07" blockId="7.[151,1436,782,1167]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97E9FBFC0EFED4FC3F" bold="true" box="[199,321,926,951]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The embolic disc (with long dPED of rounded tip, prolaterally projected and short vPED ventrally projected; 
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97E831FC52FEC6FC53" box="[269,339,962,987]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[260,1330,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[187,1392,193,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Amphidraus mysticetus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; PS, primary spermatHeca; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855441/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Figs 4</figureCitation>
C, 6C) and pattern of scales on the carapace of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF98FF97EA63FC53FC66FC53" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[863,1011,963,987]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caxiuanan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97EA63FC53FC66FC53" box="[863,1011,963,987]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">A. caxiuanan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF98FF97EAC5FC52FBC7FC53" box="[1017,1106,962,987]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97EAC5FC52FBC7FC53" bold="true" box="[1017,1106,962,987]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97ED5DFC52FB37FC53" box="[1121,1186,962,987]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,2008,2030]" captionTargetBox="[195,1396,1209,2001]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1398,1209,2001]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A male Holotype, dorsal view; B same, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855445/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A) are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF98FF97E989FC77FEDCFC76" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[181,329,999,1022]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysticetus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97E989FC77FEDCFC76" box="[181,329,999,1022]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">A. mysticetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF98FF97E873FC76FE3DFC77" box="[335,424,998,1023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97E873FC76FE3DFC77" bold="true" box="[335,424,998,1023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97E88BFC76FE6CFC77" box="[439,505,998,1023]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1876,1898]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,445,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[171,1415,445,1855]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Amphidraus mysticetus sp. nov. A carapace; B cepHalic area (different types of scales); C wHite scales; D brown scales; E left cHelicera, retrodistal view (unnamed arrows sHow promarginal teetH); F rigHt cHelicera, distal view. ALE, anterior lateral eyes; AME, anterior median eyes; PLE, posterior lateral eyes; PME, posterior median eyes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855431/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Figs 1</figureCitation>
A, 2A, 2C). However, 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF98FF97EBC6FC77FC1BFC76" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[762,910,999,1022]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caxiuanan" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97EBC6FC77FC1BFC76" box="[762,910,999,1022]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">A. caxiuanan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF98FF97EAA8FC76FC78FC77" box="[916,1005,998,1023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97EAA8FC76FC78FC77" bold="true" box="[916,1005,998,1023]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from this species in having RvTA with rounded tip (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97EB05FB9AFD14FBAB" box="[569,641,1034,1059]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[183,1377,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1412,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855449/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
D), and a straight RTA (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97EA9AFB9AFC7AFBAB" box="[934,1007,1034,1059]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[183,1377,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1412,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855449/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
B), while 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF98FF97ED5BFB9BFA95FBAB" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[1127,1280,1035,1059]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysticetus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97ED5BFB9BFA95FBAB" box="[1127,1280,1035,1059]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">A. mysticetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="87EB57E6FF98FF97EC30FB9AFAFEFBAB" box="[1292,1387,1034,1059]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" rank="species">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97EC30FB9AFAFEFBAB" bold="true" box="[1292,1387,1034,1059]" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has triangular RvTA tip (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97E8BDFBBEFE57FBCF" box="[385,450,1070,1095]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[260,1330,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[187,1392,193,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Amphidraus mysticetus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; PS, primary spermatHeca; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855441/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
D) and the RTA with the tip prolaterally curved over the cymbium (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF98FF97ED8CFBBEFB61FBCF" box="[1200,1268,1070,1095]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[260,1330,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[187,1392,193,1824]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Amphidraus mysticetus sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view; E epigyne, ventral view; F same, cleared, ventral view. CC, cymbial conductor; CO, copulatory opening; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; FD, fertilization duct; PS, primary spermatHeca; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855441/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
B). In addition, it also differs from 
<taxonomicName id="69AC4D0CFF98FF97E850FBC3FD95FBE3" authority="Ruiz, 2017" authorityName="Ruiz" authorityYear="2017" box="[364,512,1107,1131]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Amphidraus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mysticetus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF98FF97E850FBC3FD95FBE3" box="[364,512,1107,1131]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="408">A. mysticetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
