<subSubSection id="E6B66504FF97FF99E9FBF8E7FE37FEC8" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="description">
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF97FF99E9FBF8E7FB36FE95" blockId="8.[151,1436,1911,2008]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="410" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF97FF98E9FBF8E7FD5BF818" bold="true" box="[199,718,1911,1936]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
Description. Male 
<typeStatus id="7117882DFF97FF98E899F8E7FD9EF818" box="[421,523,1911,1936]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode id="C8BDAE4AFF97FF98EB26F8E7FDE5F818" box="[538,624,1911,1936]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/90vz-swjg" name="Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">MPEG</collectionCode>
29052).
</emphasis>
Total length: 2.43. Carapace with a longitudinal stripe of white scales on carapace and tufts of brown scales laterally (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF97FF98EA1EF80BFCFCF83C" box="[802,873,1947,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,2008,2030]" captionTargetBox="[195,1396,1209,2001]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1398,1209,2001]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A male Holotype, dorsal view; B same, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855445/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A), 1.33 long, 0.93 wide and 0.65 high. Ocular quadrangle 0.65 long. Anterior eye row 0.99 wide, posterior 0.84 wide. Legs: unknown (I–II lost). Length of leg III 2.44 (0.80 + 0.80 + 0.84); IV unknown (0.74 + 0.87 + broken). Palp (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99EAF9FF07FB9AFF38" box="[965,1039,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[183,1377,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1412,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855449/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Figs 6</figureCitation>
A–D): femur with a shallow distal depression, where the proximal tegular lobe fits when the palp is flexed (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99EAE7FF2CFBB5FF5D" box="[987,1056,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[183,1377,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1412,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855449/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
A); embolic filament short, about half the length of the straight, sclerotized portion (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99EBF9FF4FFC9DFF70" box="[709,776,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1744,1769]" captionTargetBox="[183,1377,193,1716]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1412,193,1716]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 6. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A left male palp, prolateral view; B same, dorsal view; C same, ventral view; D same, retrolateral view. CC, cymbial conductor; dPED, distal process on embolic disc; E, embolus; ED, embolic disc; RTA, retrolateral tibial apopHysis; RvTA, retroventral tibial apopHysis; SD, sperm duct; TL, tegular lobe; vPED, ventral process on embolic disc." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855449/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
C). Color in alcohol: thoracic area dark brown and cephalic area black; abdomen dorsally brown and variegated; ventrally pale; legs brown (
<figureCitation id="36972A0AFF96FF99ED27FE94FBC8FE95" box="[1051,1117,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,2008,2030]" captionTargetBox="[195,1396,1209,2001]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[193,1398,1209,2001]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Amphidraus caxiuanan sp. nov. A male Holotype, dorsal view; B same, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/855445/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
A–B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AE13368FFF96FF99E9FBFEB7FE37FEC8" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,418,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis id="9CD8EA9DFF96FF99E9FBFEB7FEB0FEC8" bold="true" box="[199,293,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Female.</emphasis>
